comment:
* The request object wrapping the required and optional parameters needed to fetch a {@link * CustomAudience}. * *

{@code fetchUri} is the only required parameter. It represents the URI to fetch a custom * audience from. {@code name}, {@code activationTime}, {@code expirationTime} and {@code * userBiddingSignals} are optional parameters. They represent a partial custom audience which can * be used by the caller to inform the choice of the custom audience the user should be added to. * Any field set by the caller cannot be overridden by the custom audience fetched from the {@code * fetchUri}. For more information about each field refer to {@link CustomAudience}.

methods.name: public Uri getFetchUri()
methods.comment: * @return the {@link Uri} from which the custom audience is to be fetched.

methods.name: public String getName()
methods.comment:
* Reference {@link CustomAudience#getName()} for details.
     *
     * @return the {@link String} name of the custom audience to join.

methods.name: public Instant getActivationTime()
methods.comment:
* Reference {@link CustomAudience#getActivationTime()} for details.
     *
     * @return the {@link Instant} by which joining the custom audience will be delayed.

methods.name: public Instant getExpirationTime()
methods.comment:
* Reference {@link CustomAudience#getExpirationTime()} for details.
     *
     * @return the {@link Instant} by when the membership to the custom audience will expire.

methods.name: public AdSelectionSignals getUserBiddingSignals()
methods.comment:
* Reference {@link CustomAudience#getUserBiddingSignals()} for details.
     *
     * @return the buyer signals to be consumed by the buyer-provided JavaScript when the custom
     *     audience participates in an ad selection.

methods.name: public boolean equals(Object o)
methods.comment:
* @return {@code true} only if two {@link FetchAndJoinCustomAudienceRequest} objects contain
     *     the same information.

methods.name: public int hashCode()
methods.comment: * @return the hash of the {@link FetchAndJoinCustomAudienceRequest} object's data.
